From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: suharvest <suharvest@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] v080-0012: streaming-ASR DECODE-to-transcript hook + real-audio
 spike (m6)

The streaming-ASR path (AsrStreamingSessionRuntime) could chunk-prefill audio
(byte-identical logits, proven by m1/R2) but could not emit a transcript: the
autoregressive post-prefill decode loop lived inline in
LLMInferenceRuntime::handleRequest. This patch extracts that loop into reusable
members and wires it into the streaming session so real audio -> transcript
works end to end.

1. Extract the two handleRequest decode lambdas into private members
   (allBatchesFinished, updateFinishStates) and the whole post-prefill decode
   section into decodeToCompletion(context, strategy). handleRequest now calls
   decodeToCompletion -> the one-shot path is the SAME code behind a call
   (byte-identical: m1 64/63 and 64/32 R2 max-abs logit diff 0.0, argmax MATCH;
   m2 lifecycle PASS). trajFutureStartId (an ALPAMAYO-only loop invariant) is
   recomputed inside updateFinishStates.

2. Add LLMInferenceRuntime::decodeAsrSessionToCompletion (resolves the vanilla
   cachePrimingStrategy and runs decodeToCompletion) and getAsrSessionTranscript
   (replicates the handleRequest output-extraction recipe: slice the generated
   suffix from the evicted lane's BatchResult and decode with skipSpecialTokens).

3. AsrStreamingSessionRuntime gains decodeToTranscript()/getTranscript(). Decode
   is a SEPARATE step from the final appendChunk (NOT auto-run inside it) so the
   final-chunk prefill state stays byte-identical to the prior decode-less
   behavior the m1/m2 parity spikes assert (peekKvCacheLength / getLogitsForTesting
   remain valid post-final-chunk; decodeToTranscript then evicts the lane).
   beginAsrSession gains a maxGenerateLength param (default 256): the context was
   previously initialized with maxGenLength=0, which is harmless for prefill-only
   spikes but would finish the lane after the first decoded token.

   Decode uses kVANILLA_DECODING decodeStep, NOT the chunk-prefill path, so the
   v080-0004 single-token append-prefill guard (prefill-only, in appendChunkImpl)
   never gates decode steps. Confirmed: m6 decodes 100+ tokens with no guard hit.

4. New spike examples/llm/spike_v080_m6_audio_streaming.cpp drives a real WAV's
   precomputed mel through the streaming session (encodeMelChunk ->
   appendPrefillChunk(final) -> decodeToTranscript -> transcript). Single-chunk
   mode (full WAV) and K-chunk mode (interleaved prompt).

ACCEPTANCE (Orin NX, engines-v080 Qwen3-ASR-0.6B):
  - zh_long_01 v0.8.0 STREAMING-audio transcript == v0.7.1 golden, CER 0.0000
    (norm_zh, harness edit_distance), and == v0.8.0 one-shot byte-identical.
  - zh_long_01/02/03 streaming == one-shot self-consistency CER 0.0000.
  - one-shot regression intact: m1 64/63 + 64/32 (R2 diff 0.0, argmax MATCH,
    R3 KV continuity PASS), m2 lifecycle all scenarios PASS.

